dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset is a collection of handwritten digits used for training various image processing systems. It consists of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images, each of size 28x28 pixels.

dcterms:description: The SST dataset is a sentiment analysis dataset consisting of movie reviews. It is commonly used for benchmarking natural language processing models, particularly for sentiment classification tasks.

dcterms:description: The SVHN dataset is a real-world image dataset for digit recognition, consisting of over 600,000 labeled digits from house numbers in Google Street View images. It is used for training and evaluating machine learning models.
